Currently there is no verification that the symbols used by annotations exist at all, nevermind any sense of being appropriate/correct.  This should be fixed.  Example:

```firrtl
module {
  firrtl.circuit "Oops" {
    firrtl.module private @Child() attributes {annotations = [{circt.nonlocal = @nla, class = "circt.test"}]} {
    }
    firrtl.module @Oops() {
      firrtl.instance child @Child()
    }
  }
}
```

Presently, `circt-opt` round-trips this, and `firtool` makes it all the way to `PrefixModules` before something notices.

There may be support for Attribute symbol-use verification, so look for such as that would be ideal.  Otherwise we may need to find a way to expose the uses to the symbol verifier, there are interfaces for exposing subelement's that may be appropriate here.  A final but offhand seemingly less-than-ideal approach to consider would be SymbolUserOpInterface's `verifySymbolUses` (I suppose on all our operations that take annotations).

